public class DecimalMeasure<E extends Measurable>
extends Measure<E,Real>
implements java.lang.Comparable<DecimalMeasure<E>>, Convertable<E,DecimalMeasure<E>>, Amount<DecimalMeasure<E>,E>, Scalable<E,DecimalMeasure<E>>

A real measure. DecimalMeasure is the generic and default form for explictly handle measures. You may find useful to use AngularMeasure for angular measures
